Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.76,0:00:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\N>> All right. So this is the we were trying
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.08,0:00:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to define what is the pathway of the\Nmystic. If there is such a thing and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.19,0:00:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,actually there is\Nyou seek God now through the various
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.55,0:00:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,yogas\Nthe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.16,0:00:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the various yogas have to do with\Nthe karma yoga.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.52,0:00:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The various yogas have to do with uh\Ndisciplines and meditative styles and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.32,0:00:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the yogas are explicitly defined in\NHindu classic spiritual literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.28,0:01:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the great yoga raja yoga etc\Nin uh in our world the western world uh
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.08,0:01:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,these are extremely they're very\Nwell-known classic uh mystics about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.08,0:01:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which much is written then this is the\Naerial padite 755 and I can't pronounce
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.15,0:01:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that and uh mutan matkananda\Nuh 655
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.47,0:01:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,uh St. Teresa of Aila 7:15 Wang Po 960\Nand we remember we said Wang Po
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.07,0:01:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think uh the f risen of wang po cal\N850 but wang po himself went beyond and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.28,0:01:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the pathway of negation not this\Nnot that uh netty netty not this not
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.79,0:01:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that\Nto let go of all conceptual thought
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.96,0:02:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of all concept Conceptual thought\Nis a Buddha pa p p p p p p p p p p p p p
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.36,0:02:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,p p p p p p p p p p p p p p p p p p p p\Np p p p p p pathway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.52,0:02:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what you say about anything,\Nit only amounts to something that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.47,0:02:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,saying about anything.\NI was confronted with that at age three
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.16,0:02:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is infinite reality, allness or\Nnothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.40,0:02:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,existence or or non-existence.\NNo matter what you say, existence or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.48,0:02:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence,\Nthose are both just mentalizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.68,0:02:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So why bother saying either one?\NDon't bother with existence or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.40,0:02:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence. Forget about it. Let God\Nworry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.23,0:02:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are just statements. Statements\Nabout how the mind sees things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.31,0:03:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So what they're really saying through\Nthat pathway of negation then is that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.12,0:03:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that your mind says is a\Nperception
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.28,0:03:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise it couldn't say anything\Nbecause it is stuck in perceptions you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.51,0:03:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot find divinity or the Buddha\Nnature uh through the mind. So
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.92,0:03:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend the mind is critical.\NTo transcend the mind with a small M
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.40,0:03:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which opens the way for mind with a\Ncapital M.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.12,0:03:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither existence nor non-existence.\NSo it took I forget 36 years to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.84,0:03:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend that dilemma. Is the reality\Nexistence or is it non-existence?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.15,0:03:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot say each one of them is a\Ndefinition. Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.84,0:03:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So Hangpo is one of my favorite\Nteachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.51,0:04:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Patangeli at 7:15. Plutinus at 7:30.\NRama Krishna at 6:20. Raman Maharshi and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.76,0:04:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Maharaj\Nuh are at 7:20. So the book we just
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,finished which is pretty much focused on\Nthis level calibrates I don't know 720
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.40,0:04:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to 740 because we're trying to focus on\Nthe differentiation between perception
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.47,0:04:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and essence\Nwhen mana says don't worry about the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.52,0:04:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,world you see because the world you see\Ndoesn't even exist it makes no sense to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.47,0:04:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the average person what do you mean the\Nworld you see doesn't even exist
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so 720 to 740 cal uh clarifies\Nyou know the difference between
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.84,0:04:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,perception and essence and what the\Nworld sees of course and thinks is truth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.16,0:04:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is perception. What it thinks is truth\Nis nothing but perception and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.16,0:04:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is devoid of any inner reality.\NOne TV news program is just as facious
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.40,0:05:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as the next.\NSt. John of the Cross. The some of these
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,are so well known and uh you know books\Nare available about them and I always
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.03,0:05:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,liked her this name Mild Deaf Machber\Nsounds so delightfully Germanic doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.32,0:05:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it? Yeah.\NSt. Francis of Aisi of course we're all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.36,0:05:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar with. So I put in those that\Nwere most famous. St. Dominic of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.60,0:05:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Dominican order.\Nuh Meister Ehart of course who's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.88,0:05:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely well known and got into some\Ntrouble with the Catholic Church over
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.91,0:05:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,his mysticism\Nand then there is a famous book uh it's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.68,0:05:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a really central to mysticism called the\Ncloud of unknowing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.19,0:05:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,uh which calibrates at 700 the cloud of\Nunknowing has an unknown author
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.47,0:05:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and I always wanted to write books\Nanonymously ly first book power versus
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to I wanted it to be anonymous\Nbecause there's no person saying this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.91,0:06:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,there's any person saying this\Nthis happens after this it doesn't need
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.31,0:06:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a person to say it and I thought putting\Nin a person as an author
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.44,0:06:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh detracts from the truth of what is\Nbeing written so the wisdom of the cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.88,0:06:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of unknowing is you I don't have an\Nauthor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.03,0:06:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,uh that you can go online with and\Ncriticize.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.63,0:06:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Puggy Whipwick. He doesn't know his\Nass from Hot Rock and you know he's he
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.56,0:06:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds like a leftist to me. Sound like\Na conservative or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.12,0:06:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That propensity to politicize\Neverything. You know, I like a bagel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nso you want to you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.75,0:06:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right away that's a political Oh, bagel.\NHuh? Huh? What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.96,0:07:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not trying to say anything. You\Njust want to have lunch. You know what
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.28,0:07:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying? All right, we'll move to the\Nnext one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.72,0:07:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have five on the mystic. Is that\Ncorrect? Yeah. All right. So, I know how
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.03,0:07:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to time us. How much time we got left?\NHuh? 20 minutes. Oh, good. We can go to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.08,0:07:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the moon and back in 20 minutes.\NSo the pathway of the mystic then is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.24,0:07:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,very much aligned with consciousness\Ncalibration and the kind of work we've
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.80,0:07:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,been doing here because what we try to\Ndifferentiate is perception from essence
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.28,0:07:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,not to be fueled by fooled by\Nperception.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.52,0:07:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what people consider to be myself I. You\Nhave to transcend the personal eye and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.31,0:07:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,this is why it is difficult to transcend\Nthe personal eye is almost impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:08:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for the majority of people. Therefore,\Nenlightenment is chosen by
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.03,0:08:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,one out of 10 million people.\NYou ask what is your highest goal in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,this life? Only one in 10 million will\Nsay become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.24,0:08:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, it's extremely rare, is it\Nnot? If only one in 10 million even
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.08,0:08:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,choose it.\NLook how rare it must be. And out of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.24,0:08:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,those who choose it, what percentage are\Nsuccessful? Yes. Because eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.68,0:08:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,great sacrifices are necessary that go\Nthe whole way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.12,0:08:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,People identify themsel as their age,\Ntheir body, their sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.95,0:08:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the information from their senses and\Nhow old they are and they also identify
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.92,0:08:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,themsel as an animal.\NWe have an animal side to our nature. We
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.08,0:08:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,have both the spiritual side and also\Nthe animal side. So we have difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.24,0:09:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because many most of the classic\Nreligions tend to vilify the animal
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.80,0:09:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,side.\NCarnal carnal
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.32,0:09:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for carnality, there\Nwouldn't be anybody around here to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.27,0:09:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,complain about carnality.\NIf it wasn't for sexual desire, nobody
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.44,0:09:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,would even exist in the physical plane.\NAll right? So, you're supposed to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.64,0:09:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,repudiate. Well, what it really means is\Nto stop being run by it. Lust, not to be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.83,0:09:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,run by lust. It doesn't mean you got to\Nbe dead sexually,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.68,0:09:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,although there's a cure for that. on\Ntelevision. I notice
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.44,0:09:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,how to reawaken your animal nature.\NSo people identify automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.72,0:09:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as most importantly as the doer,\Nthe decider, the chooser, the one who
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.12,0:10:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,feels, who who wants, who doesn't like,\Nwho makes decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.20,0:10:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And in all the previous lectures we try\Nto emphasize that there is no you making
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.27,0:10:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,any decisions about anything at all.\NThat is all 100% illusion. There is no
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.48,0:10:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,personal you that is deciding you know\Nwhat to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.56,0:10:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's happening autonomously.\NAnd you arrive at that observation as
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.72,0:10:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you remove identifying as the personal\Nself and move into the witness observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.68,0:10:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The witness and the observer\Nnotices that as soon as a decision is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.80,0:10:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,made or something happens there's a\Nsense a personal eye jumps in there and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.48,0:10:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,claims authorship.\NSo the hardest thing to get over as a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.27,0:11:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,habit of mind is the claiming of\Nauthorship of a personal eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.20,0:11:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no personal eye making any\Ndecisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.68,0:11:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is happening autonomously\Nincluding the illusion that there is a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.95,0:11:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,personal eye.\NTherefore, you don't have to feel guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.88,0:11:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,about considering yourself to be an\Nindependent decider and initiator of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.92,0:11:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,actions and thoughts and feelings\Nbecause even that is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.39,0:11:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,autonomously\Nwithout asking your permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.07,0:11:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you have a presumption. There is a\Npersonal you that is the initiator and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.27,0:11:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,decider and the doer.\NThe jump ahead of this illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.72,0:11:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be done faster than 110,000th of\Na second.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.07,0:11:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The leading edge of the ego, the\Npersonal eye
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.32,0:12:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,instantly jumps in in one 10,000 of a\Nsecond and cla and claims to be the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.64,0:12:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,author, the initiator and the\Nexperiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.63,0:12:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,through the spiritual\Nstyles we've been describing, it is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.83,0:12:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,possible to transcend\Ntranscend that. And the mind then
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.07,0:12:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes silent. People say, "Well, I've\Ntried to silence my mind for years and I
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.80,0:12:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,can't do it." The harder I try to just\Nsilence it, the more vigorous it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.04,0:12:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes.\NAnd it's because they're looking for it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.12,0:12:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in a linear Newtonian dimension of\Ncausality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.36,0:12:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They're looking for a mind here that's\Ncausing a thought or an action there and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,then claiming authorship.\NThat's a Newtonian dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.20,0:12:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you find the silent source of\Nall the inner phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.83,0:13:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is underneath. I I always say there's a\Nblankness underneath thinkingness. Don't
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.32,0:13:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,try to stop thinking this because you'll\Njust end up as the person who's trying
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.00,0:13:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop thinking this\Nor you'll end up as the person who
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.92,0:13:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't want to think of about himself\Nas I but he does or otherwise he
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.44,0:13:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't be trying to transcend that I\Nthink about myself as I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.72,0:13:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,your foot gets stuck in the gum no\Nmatter what you do you know get the gum
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.32,0:13:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,off this shoe and it's stuck on this\Nshoe
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.00,0:13:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you get rid of the gum\NThe sequential thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.12,0:13:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and endless bo babble of nonsense having\Nto do with nothing but perception and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.20,0:13:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not with essence anyway is totally\Nworthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.00,0:13:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All your thoughts including your most\Ntreasured wonderful thoughts that you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.60,0:13:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,have embroidered surrounded with silver\Nand gold are worth nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.39,0:14:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So you start with humility.\Nthat all thoughts are worth nothing at
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,all. They're amusement. And where do you\Nlook then for the source of the self?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.39,0:14:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You look, you don't look amongst\Nthoughts. You can't find it there. You
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.88,0:14:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,look underneath the field of thoughts.\NNow, thoughts are like the waves on the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.12,0:14:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,sea coming and going, coming and going.\NThe waves are always coming and going.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.60,0:14:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you silence the surface of the\Nocean? You can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.88,0:14:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you find any stillness on the\Nocean? You can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.80,0:14:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The nature of the ocean is to have\Nlittle waves and big waves and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.60,0:14:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,called oceanness.\NSo the stillness is below the surface of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.68,0:14:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the ocean, not on the surface of the\Nocean. Trying to silence the mind on the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.24,0:14:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,level of the waves on the surface of the\Nmind is feudal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.12,0:15:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you dive below the mind underneath\Nthinkingness. Below thinkingness a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.83,0:15:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,priori\Nprior to the thinkingness is an infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.27,0:15:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,field an energy field of silence.\NThe silence is present now even as
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.56,0:15:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you listen to the words\Nthat which is speaking is nonsensical.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.92,0:15:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a peripheral phenomena.\NI don't need talking in the slightest
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.16,0:15:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,bit. Could dispense with him about the\Nslightest. Goodbye. Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.00,0:15:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the hints.\NUnderneath that talkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.76,0:15:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is an infinite profound sense of\Nsilence. This is the infinite field of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.51,0:15:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the self with a capital S, the Buddha\Nnature, the field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.56,0:15:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NYou don't have to join an ash ram and do
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.72,0:15:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of weird things and eat weird\Nfood and go through weird exercises to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.04,0:16:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,find that which is right obvious below\Nthe surface and constantly present.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.19,0:16:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Sorry.\NGuards
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.51,0:16:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,arrest this infidel.\NTrying to penetrate the silence. Get you
