Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.40,1:38:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the supersonics did not have a single\Naccident for what was it 26 years or
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.80,1:38:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,something and then one got a flat tire\Nand that brought down the whole
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.80,1:38:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,industry? I don't believe that. Do you?\NYou think the whole industry collapsed
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.96,1:38:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because one supersonic got a flat tire\Non the tarmac? I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.44,1:38:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't had time to check it out with\Nthe arm. You know, there's so many
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.08,1:38:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,things we could check out.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.36,1:38:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, sir.\N>> I'm glad you're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.04,1:38:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, sir.\N>> How do you say it in Korean? What do you
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.88,1:38:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,say?\N>> Say it to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.28,1:38:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Ka.\N>> Hello, Dr. Hawkins. Such a a gift today.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.28,1:39:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\N>> That's mine. Yeah. Um the question I
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.84,1:39:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have that I would really like to know I\Nfind I get confused by um you speak of
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.00,1:39:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no doer and there is no\Nrecipient. We're not making choices
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.92,1:39:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and then\N>> there is no personal self.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.67,1:39:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no personal self.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.96,1:39:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> so how do we get um the wrong choices\Nlike the false gurus or the could we not
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.28,1:39:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,just surrender and if you end up with\Nthe wrong at the wrong place at the then
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.80,1:39:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't end up at the wrong place at\Nthe wrong time. Is that what I'm
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.67,1:39:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,hearing?\N>> No, I'm talking about the idea
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.08,1:39:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that the originator that all the\Nintention is coming from an independent
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.40,1:39:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,personal self. actually it's not coming\Nfrom that. So
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.19,1:40:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the personal self says well I decided to\Nsign the book. I a separate personal
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.44,1:40:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,self is the initiator of this action now\Ntaking place.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.23,1:40:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Not God.\N>> The ego says there's a personal eye
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.04,1:40:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,doing this. In reality there isn't a\Npersonal eye doing this.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.96,1:40:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> As a consequence of the totality of this\Nwhole situation now present. this arm
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.40,1:40:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,goes forward and signs it because that's\Nthe expectation
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.40,1:40:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that is in the air. You might say,\N"Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.48,1:40:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there isn't any personal self making a\Ndecision."
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.36,1:40:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as an action occurs,\Nthe personal self jumps in in one
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.40,1:40:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,thousandth of a second and claims, "Oh,\NI decided to sign these books.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.88,1:40:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't decide to sign these books at\Nall.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.04,1:40:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I didn't know anything about it. She\Nhands them over and the arm goes like
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.15,1:41:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,this. And I say to myself, should I sign\Nthese? I don't know. I didn't ask
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.52,1:41:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,myself, did I?\NSo all of life is is emergent rather
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.52,1:41:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,than causal.\NThe potentiality emerges for this to
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.36,1:41:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,happen. It's not caused by anything.\NIf it was caused, there would be no
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.19,1:41:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom. Therefore, there'd be no karma.\NThere'd be no freedom because all
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.44,1:41:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,everything would be determined. So\Nto believe in a personal eye is to
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.96,1:41:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,believe in really materialistic\Nreductionism and naive causality
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.23,1:41:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of primitive Newtonian cause\Ncausality.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.88,1:41:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the totality of the universe.\NTotality of the universe throughout all
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.44,1:42:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of time\N>> that that that
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.71,1:42:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is responsible for this arm moving in\Nfront of you this moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.96,1:42:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the last second, this second\Ncouldn't occur, could it?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.19,1:42:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It took the evolution of all It took all\Nof evolution, of all of creation, all of
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.88,1:42:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,time to reach the point where this arm\Nreaches out and signs this book.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.84,1:42:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.76,1:42:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The awareness does not arise out of\Nreason. It arise out of sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.28,1:42:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,intuiting.\Nthat everything that happens is is it's
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.28,1:42:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a consequence of the of of the whole,\Nnot of the part.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.19,1:42:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi, we don't have a question. We just\Nwanted to sit across from you and thank
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.88,1:42:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you.\N>> What?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.44,1:42:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,>> We just wanted to sit across from you\Nand thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.63,1:43:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes,\N>> that's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.63,1:43:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, thank you.\N>> Oh, I got a freebie, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.52,1:43:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, Susan.\N>> Oh, thank you. so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.71,1:43:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> This won't hurt, will it?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.28,1:43:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah, that's what the guy says. Does it\Nhurt? No, only when I laugh.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.36,1:43:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah, I don't have a question either. I\Njust wanted to sit here and be with you
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.80,1:43:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> your presence and thank you.\N>> Uh yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.60,1:43:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I'll tell you a story as long as you're\Nhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.52,1:43:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay, sure.\N>> This cowboy is out in the country by
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.28,1:43:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,himself and he hears this groaning\Ncoming from behind a rock.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.40,1:43:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes around the rock and there's a\Ncowboy laying there with an arrow
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.60,1:44:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,through his chest. He says, "Oh my god,\Nman. Doesn't that hurt?" This is only
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.15,1:44:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when I laugh.\N>> That's funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.60,1:44:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you for the story.\NThank you, S.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.11,1:44:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right.\N>> That's a funny punchline.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.71,1:44:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use it once in a while in life.\NYou know, say, "Well, how is something?"
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.56,1:44:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, "Only when I laugh." Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.60,1:45:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hallelujah.\NHallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.76,1:45:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah.\NHallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.19,1:45:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah.
